 :demo: /de'moh/ [short for `demonstration'] 1. v. To demonstrate a product
or prototype. A far more effective way of inducing bugs to manifest than any
number of {test} runs, especially when important people are watching. 2. n.
The act of demoing. 3. n. Esp. as `demo version', can refer to either a
special version of a program (frequently with some features crippled) which
is distributed at little or no cost to the user for demonstration purposes.